going to partake of the first-fruits of the harvest, is\ntreated of, with relation to a sacrificer who keeps the _S_ rauta fires, in\nthe _S_ rauta-sutra II, q. This Sutra in my opinion should be understood as a\nsupplementary addition to that chapter. Naraya _n_ a refers the rule here\ngiven to the case of any incident or danger (apad) which prevents the\nsacrificer from performing the ceremony in its fuller form, as prescribed in\nthe _S_ rauta-sutra.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 3](sbe29126.htm)\n\n'